00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:11.000
Light is mission-critical for mankind.

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:16.000
Light is the most important 
thing in nature that we have. 

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:21.000
If there will be no Sun on this 
planet in 20 minutes from now,

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:27.000
there will be no life anymore. innovation 
doesn't happen in a vacuum anymore, it's

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:29.000
something you do together.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:33.000
it's really important to team up with designers,

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:36.000
specifiers, engineers, architect specialists

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
in sciences and put together 
a team that collaboratively

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
works on the same objectives. 
Open innovation is

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
all about what you do with all these kinds of

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
game-changing technologies. 
I think that makes it so relevant

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
to collaborate and on top of 
that it makes it so much fun

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:57.500
because

00:00:57.500 --> 00:01:00.500
we learn every day from the teamwork.

00:01:00.500 --> 00:01:04.500
You know, with the lighting designers, 
with the architects, we take the architects

00:01:04.500 --> 00:01:07.500
with us in the lab and in the 
Application Centers that we have.

00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:12.500
They see people who know a lot about 
lights, but about the lights that they’ve

00:01:12.500 --> 00:01:16.500
already made, not about the products of the future

00:01:16.500 --> 00:01:23.000
that we can co-create together with those 
designers and architects. It's a very

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:27.000
personal question of course to talk 
about inspiration because we all

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:29.000
experience it differently
 
